originalText.text:
Decent people, gave it a chance but a shop is a shop, don't usually use OEM parts even if available apparently, needed valve cover, gasket, coils and spark plugs, checked coils they are fine, 50 minutes labor time to change out spark plugs? If you're already taking out a valve cover on a 4 cylinder why is spark plug labor included and or why so much? Also apparently lost my shark fin antenna, cars are left outside sometimes in a not so great area so maybe it was vandalized, also they broke a piece of the plastic where one of the liner fasteners go to secure the intake I'm guessing while replacing the radiator fan, small damages that might or might not add up and they won't ever be liable for.

Years ago i also had my car towed to this place to get a new battery, after a few months battery was leaking had to get a new one.

Update: Car is now leaking all the coolant, yeah i would not recommend this shop.
